Harvard’s Feldstein Sees 50% Chance of U.S. Sliding Back Into a Recession

-- B y   C h r i s   W e l l i s z   a n d   T o m   K e e n e
-- 
2011-08-02T16:37:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/harvard-s-feldstein-sees-50-chance-of-u-s-sliding-back-into-a-recession.html
Harvard University economics
professor Martin Feldstein said he sees a 50 percent chance of a
renewed recession in the U.S.  “Nothing has given us much growth,” Feldstein said today
in a Bloomberg Television interview on “Surveillance Midday”
with  Tom Keene . Feldstein is a member of the committee that 
dates recessions for the  National Bureau of Economic Research .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Wellisz at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net  